					<div class="commentheading">On March 11, 2007 at 03:40 AM, an anonymous reader said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>great adaptation</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">in search of a recipe for the old standard comfort food, this site appeared.  Politicizing aside, try this:<br />
<br />
brown rice instead of white (maybe some other grains mixed in)<br />
Amy's Organic cream of mushroom soup<br />
brown the (organic) chicken parts<br />
increase the water (I increased to 3.5-4 cups)<br />
use a combination of water, organic chicken broth and a spot of milk/cream<br />
add thyme, parsley &amp; black pepper<br />
a bit of salt (yes, have to add some because soup is low sodium)<br />
increase the garlic and skip the onions (if this is to your taste).<br />
cook in an iron skillet<br />
<br />
Such comfort for a rainy day in the Pacific NW!</div>
