					<div class="commentbody">Actually worked out pretty well. After an hour the rice and chicken were both cooked, although there were a couple of slightly underdone parts in the thickest part of the largest breasts. <br />
<br />
There was too much liquid and not enough visible rice, so I picked the meat off the bones and added it back in small pieces. Then there wasn't enough liquid, so I added another beer and some leftover kimchi... and just to get the flames going again, a bit of half-and-half cream ;)<br />
<br />
End result had a pretty good chicken a la king kind of taste/texture. Will try it over toast in the morning.</div>
